#23. Explain how connect yourself as new user. (With graphic session and ssh session)

Ans : i
   1. connect to a ssh session,
      in /etc/ssh/sshd_config

	  specify the following:

	  Port 1234
	  PermitRootLogin no
	  allowUsers jim
	  

	  Above specification means use jim is allowed to 
	  login by connect to port 1234.

	 a.  ssh remotehost -  is the command-ine for ssh session. 


  2.  connect with graphic session

	 a. specify X11Forwarding yes in the server configuration file.
     b. %ssh remotehost(ipaddr) 	 (from client side)


